race.comment: AHVEJAY (2) was a determined winner three back here. Has been less effective in his last two but is at peak fitness now and keeps the claimer on to help at the weights. Should blend into the race nicely from his draw and is one of the key hopes. SO REGAL (7) made light work of his maiden two back at Horsham but struggled to follow it up last time when getting too far back from the wide gate. Draws better this time and should be more handy. Can bounce back. CROWN AND ANCHOR (8) was good fresh but responsible for a flat effort second-up. Freshened with 6 weeks and can improve sharply. LUCKY COMPASS (14) best of the rest.
